ibrary at Nanterre</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_44563b58ed65ce215ae215d3865c4554" level="file"><did><unittitle>PRO - PREM 314 + FO</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1945/1945">1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_cf11577154b29f5e9a4a384006a2ad6a" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_fb381d5d7a7673ccd0d3cdd7f5990ab0" parent="aspace_cf11577154b29f5e9a4a384006a2ad6a" type="folder">5-6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_669fb89da0b2e7f65b08d266a15294ea"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Classified documents on French Indo-China from Public Records Office (Foreign Office documents)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_40e26f05a69d014871b2b4106e486296" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mary Speers' Notes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1942/1943" type="inclusive">1942-1943</unitdate><container id="aspace_5559f7c6258e62e82564fed61515833b" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c189f3a04434366df55ce80241e17191" parent="aspace_5559f7c6258e62e82564fed61515833b" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2fb37c646720f4ad11ac37885ab965b4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Foreign Office series 371/35921, ff. Mostly on wartime relations with France.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_66374441566d62f006507bd57881470f" level="file"><did><unittitle>My Notes 1980 - PRO &amp; Rhodes House</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1980/1980">1980</unitdate><container id="aspace_f9f949937c3288393a0ce5d743f8cc7e" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_50b11574a7b15636358a54f845b8d21f" parent="aspace_f9f949937c3288393a0ce5d743f8cc7e" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_15da68ac1d332fa320352b6d9de99815"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "My Notes 1980: PRO &amp; Roosevelt." CAB 120/56 - 121/741. Succinct notes of heart of documents re: French Indochina (ca. 40-50 pp.). Notebook cover headed "Cabinet Officers etc." has several pages of references to A. Creech Jones.</p><p> 2nd notebook: Rhodes Library Oxford - About 100 pp. of penciled notes on FO 371; CO 824 Register; CO 872-4-9 inclusive (1942, 1942) Mostly to FO 371/371779-90</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_882641775d4bd943c4046cce71f4aac7" level="file"><did><unittitle>DDE '54 - documents</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1954/1954">1954</unitdate><container id="aspace_65273d5a2554b2cb8068099b5c3e9615" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_a4318901ac8c14cc564057ccfd205069" parent="aspace_65273d5a2554b2cb8068099b5c3e9615" type="folder">9</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_d4c4cd2d8b44f1177511b9a1ffa9da65"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Dwight D. Eisenhower Library</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_42adfae9cae0b88bcf98f8b0bf2e8c14" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives - Use of Indo China Resistance Forces</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1944/1945" type="inclusive">1944-1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_b15551fcf34eff042d68e82081054fec" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_a9961a9373ffb4a923d3d71f913c8afc" parent="aspace_b15551fcf34eff042d68e82081054fec" type="folder">10-11</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_dbd8f8d86f47433c2d61b3b65e326d31" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1941/1941">1941</unitdate><container id="aspace_2189350167d6fc192d4b91370909089a" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c1b580b3b87dc8aa02203cee24eab17d" parent="aspace_2189350167d6fc192d4b91370909089a" type="folder">12</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_88f942e2113e